NAME "Crusher"

-- Mekanism Crusher automation (mekanism:crushing recipe type)
-- Covers every crushing recipe registered by any mod in the pack, since
-- addon mods add recipes to Mekanism's own recipe type rather than adding
-- their own crusher block. The Crusher is a single-input/single-output
-- machine, so unlike the Reaction Chamber there's no RETAIN combo needed --
-- just keep every valid input material stocked and drain the result.
-- Labels needed:
--   Barrel  => input chest/barrel with all raw materials
--   Crusher => all Mekanism Crusher machines
--   Storage => output storage
--   Battery => power source (capacitor bank, energy cell, etc) feeding the crushers
--
-- MEKANISM GOTCHA: unlike the AE2/ExtendedAE machines in this pack,
-- Mekanism blocks expose per-face IO configuration (the colored side
-- config screen, opened by right-clicking the machine with the
-- Configurator). A face that isn't configured to accept energy will not
-- receive power even though the block has the capability. SFM lets you
-- target a specific face directly with a side qualifier (see the
-- bundled "Slots and sides" example program): "<label> <direction> side"
-- placed right after the label. Below assumes you configured the TOP
-- face of every Crusher as the Energy input (red) -- change "top" to
-- whichever face you actually set in-game.

-- Keep every Crusher topped up. Energy is a scalar resource type in SFM
-- -- "fe::" expands to sfm:fe:*:* (any FE/RF/energy/power literal all
-- alias to the same forge_energy resource type). A literal "forge:energy"
-- is NOT the same thing: that's parsed as an item lookup for a
-- (nonexistent) item named forge:energy and silently moves nothing.
EVERY 1 TICKS DO
    INPUT FROM Battery TOP SIDE
    OUTPUT fe:: TO EACH Crusher TOP SIDE
    FORGET
END

EVERY REDSTONE PULSE DO

